 social science through the use of chaos and complexity theory as an inspiration for understanding the structures of contemporary social life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCity dwellersxLanguagezBelgiumzAntwerp. 0aEthnicityzBelgiumzAntwerp. 0aLanguages in contactzBelgiumzAntwerp. 0aLinguistic minoritieszBelgiumzAntwerp. 0aMultilingualismzBelgiumzAntwerp. 0aSociolinguisticszBelgiumzAntwerp. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aAntwerp.  acomplexity.  aconviviality.  aethnography.  alinguistic landscapes.  alinguistic landscaping.  amigration.  amultilingual signs.  amultiliteracies.  amultimodality.  asociolinguistic landscapes.  asuperdiversity.1 aBlommaert, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKubota, Ryuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPennycook, Alastair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102473808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106067130 cprintz978178309040240uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309041940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783090419423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783090419/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102473-8  MultiLingual Mat